Provide engineering, scientific, analytical, and managerial support to the Office of the Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defense for Research in:
•	Developing strategies, plans, and policies to develop and exploit technology; 
•	Conducting technology analyses, making recommendations, and developing guidance for S&T plans and programs;
•	Reviewing acquisition programs and making recommendations to optimize effectiveness of the DoD investments; and
•	Oversight of S&T issues and initiatives and responding to Congressional special interests.

Seek opportunities for interdepartmental and international cooperation in high priority S&T. Conduct intradepartmental coordination to achieve goals as necessary.

